cards.description:
Comments: This field is for internal CNDDB purposes (notes to fellow CNDDBers) and is not viewed by others outside of CNDDB. Enter plant population size here.
 Example: "23 plants" or "~10-20 plants"
 Why the source was treated a particular way:
o Does not meet EO definition (nesting)
o Rejected because...
o Duplicateof...,samedataas...,similarto...,etc o Transcribed by CNDDB
 This is not a required field and oftentimes it will be left blank.
cards.name: Comments

graph.name: Sources

nodes.description: Affiliation: Choose from the dropdown list; just start typing. For example, if the affiliation is Chambers Group, start typing until this appears in the list; then chose the correct affiliation. New affiliations must be added by Joe V, so either email your lead or Joe.
nodes.name: Affiliation

nodes.description:
Author: Author name (tab to the next field so that first 3 letters of last name auto-populate the field at the far right).
Format:
1 author:
Last name, first initial.
Elliott, R.
2 authors:
Last name, first initial & First initial, last name Elliott, R. & R. Bittman
>2 authors
Last name, first initial et al. (et al. = et alii, “and others”) Elliott, R. et al.
*In some cases we may prefer that the 3 letter author code be changed to be more abbreviation-like. A common example is for Museum of Vertebrate Zoology we prefer the 3 letter code to be “MVZ” instead of “MUS.” Or, for US Fish and Wildlife Service we would prefer FWS as opposed to USF or FIS. See Sourcing Tips & Tricks for further details.
nodes.name: Document Author

nodes.description: Intent is to zip up all of the files associated to the legacy source record (pdf, shp, excel, etc) and store them here until such time they can be processed into regular observations records.
nodes.name: Legacy Files

nodes.description:
Title: Title of source document. If the source is a field survey form (source type F), this will automatically be populated once you tab off of “Source Type.” Note: If you copy past (F6) from a previous form into a new form and change the scientific name (this is for the field survey form only) you must change the scientific name for the field survey form in the title field.
See Sourcing Tips & Tricks document for details and examples of writing titles for other types of sources, like reports (R), Scientific Collecting Permits, unpublished (U) documents, etc.
nodes.name: Document Title

nodes.description: Location: This field may be ignored. It is filled in when the data is mapped. This is not the location in California; it is the location of where the document is filed away at CNDDB.
nodes.name: Location Description
